{"id":53,"parent_id":50,"book_id":9398,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":53,"title":"Luke 3: John Baptizes the Son of God","subtitle":"","short_title":"Luke 3: John Baptizes the Son of God","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-luke/luke-3-john-baptizes-the-son-of-god","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-luke/luke-3-john-baptizes-the-son-of-god"},[".heading",{"id":"head4","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-luke/luke-3-john-baptizes-the-son-of-god.head4"},["h1","Luke 3"],[".subtitle","John Baptizes the Son of God"],[".intro","John the Baptist and Jesus were cousins (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/1.36"},"Luke 1:36"],"), and John was just six months older than Jesus. He was sent to prepare the way for the mission of Jesus Christ. As you study",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/3"},"Luke 3"],", look for what John taught the people and the ways it would help them be ready to hear the Savior. Be sure to read the Joseph Smith Translation additions to this chapter, which tell us more about the mission of Jesus Christ."]],[".bodyBlock",[".topic",["h2","Other Accounts of What You Read in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/3"},"Luke 3"]],["p.para",{"id":"p85","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-luke/luke-3-john-baptizes-the-son-of-god.p85"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/3.1-22"},"Luke 3:1–22"],"—",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/3"},"Matthew 3"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/1.2-11"},"Mark 1:2–11"]],["p.para",{"id":"p86","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-luke/luke-3-john-baptizes-the-son-of-god.p86"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/3.23-38"},"Luke 3:23–38"],"—",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/1.1-17"},"Matthew 1:1–17"]]],[".topic",["h2","Understanding the Scriptures"],[".figure",{"id":"f12","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-luke/luke-3-john-baptizes-the-son-of-god.f12"},["p"],["h2",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/3"},"Luke 3"]],["p"],["table",["tbody",["tr",["td",["b","Tetrarch"],"(v. 1)"],["td","Ruler or governor"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Remission"],"(v. 3)"],["td","Forgiveness"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","The wrath to come"],"(v. 7)"],["td","The coming judgments of God"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Fruits worthy of repentance"],"(v. 8)"],["td","Actions that demonstrate true repentance"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Ax is laid unto the root of the trees"],"(v. 9)"],["td","See “Understanding the Scriptures” for",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/3.10"},"Matthew 3:10"],"(p. 12)"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Hewn"],"(v. 9)"],["td","Cut"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Publicans"],"(v. 12)"],["td","Tax collectors"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Exact"],"(v. 13)"],["td","Take, collect"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Content"],"(v. 14)"],["td","Satisfied"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Mused"],"(v. 15)"],["td","Thought about"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Latchet"],"(v. 16)"],["td","Laces or straps"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Fan"],"(v. 17)"],["td","A tool or instrument used to separate wheat kernels from their lighter outer shell (chaff) that is not eaten"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Purge his floor"],"(v. 17)"],["td","Clean his place of harvesting"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Exhortation"],"(v. 18)"],["td","A speech to encourage and strengthen"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Reproved"],"(v. 19)"],["td","Scolded, rebuked"],["td"]]]]],[".",{"id":"f13","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-luke/luke-3-john-baptizes-the-son-of-god.f13"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/p-055-2.gif"}],[".caption",["p",{"id":"lds-"},["span.emphasis","Separating wheat from chaff"]]]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/3.8-9"},"Luke 3:8–9"],"—“We Have Abraham to Our Father”"],["p.para",{"id":"p103","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-luke/luke-3-john-baptizes-the-son-of-god.p103"},"The Lord made great promises to Abraham because of his faithfulness (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/13.14-17"},"Genesis 13:14–17"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/abr/2.8-11"},"Abraham 2:8–11"],"). Many Jews believed that they would be saved simply because they were the descendants of Abraham (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/jst/jst-luke/3.13"},"JST,Luke 3:13"],"). John the Baptist told them that if they did not repent, they would be cut down like useless trees. This teaching emphasized that we will be judged by our works, and that only the righteous receive eternal life."]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/3.19-20"},"Luke 3:19–20"],"—What Had Herod Done Wrong?"],["p.para",{"id":"p104","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-luke/luke-3-john-baptizes-the-son-of-god.p104"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/3.19-20"},"Luke 3:19–20"],"refers to Herod Antipas, the tetrarch. He was the son of Herod the Great, whom you read about in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/2"},"Matthew 2"],". Herod Antipas left his first wife to marry his niece Herodias, who had been married to his brother Philip. Such a marriage was against the law of Moses (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/lev/20.21"},"Leviticus 20:21"],"). When John the Baptist called him to repent, Herod had John thrown into prison."]]],[".topic",["h2","Studying the Scriptures"],["p.para",{"id":"p105","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-luke/luke-3-john-baptizes-the-son-of-god.p105"},"Do the three following activities (A–C) as you study",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/3"},"Luke 3"],"."],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-a.gif"}],"John Prepares the Way"],[".figure",{"id":"f14","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-luke/luke-3-john-baptizes-the-son-of-god.f14"},["ol.number",["li",["span.label","1."],["p.para","Review",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/3.7-14"},"Luke 3:7–14"],"and list the “fruits worthy of repentance” that John told the people to “bring forth” (v. 8)."]],["li",["span.label","2."],["p.para","Write about how each of these fruits would help us prepare to meet the Savior."]]]]],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-b.gif"}],"What Should We Do?"],["p.para",{"id":"p108","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-luke/luke-3-john-baptizes-the-son-of-god.p108"},"After John the Baptist taught the people that every tree that would not grow good fruit would be cut down and “cast into the fire” (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/3.9"},"Luke 3:9"],"), the people asked, “What shall we do then?” (v. 10). John then gave some examples of what it meant to bring forth good fruit."],[".figure",{"id":"f15","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-luke/luke-3-john-baptizes-the-son-of-god.f15"},["ol.number",["li",["span.label","1."],["p.para","List what John suggested for:"],[".figure",{"id":"f","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide.f"},["ol.alphaLowCase",["li",["span.label","a."],["p.para","People with food and clothing"]],["li",["span.label","b."],["p.para","Publicans"]],["li",["span.label","c."],["p.para","Soldiers"]]]]],["li",["span.label","2."],["p.para","Based on what John taught, write what you think he would suggest today for:"],[".figure",{"id":"f","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide.f"},["ol.alphaLowCase",["li",["span.label","a."],["p.para","Teenagers at school"]],["li",["span.label","b."],["p.para","Children living with their parents"]],["li",["span.label","c."],["p.para","Parents"]]]]]]]],[".",{"id":"f18","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-luke/luke-3-john-baptizes-the-son-of-god.f18"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/p-056-1.gif"}]],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-c.gif"}],"Choose a Symbol"],[".figure",{"id":"f19","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-luke/luke-3-john-baptizes-the-son-of-god.f19"},["ol.number",["li",["span.label","1."],["p.para","Explain what each of the following words found in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/3.7-18"},"Luke 3:7–18"],"could symbolize in the message or mission of John the Baptist:",["span.emphasis","vipers, stones, fruit, roots, shoes, wheat."]]],["li",["span.label","2."],["p.para","Choose one of the above symbols that people you know would be",["span.emphasis","least"],"likely to relate to. Think of a different symbol that people in your area might better understand. Describe how you would use it to teach a principle John taught."]]]]]]],[".resources"]]]],"refs":null}
